Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have attracted tremendous attention for their combination of environmental power generation and fuel flexibility.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode

Sentencas: Proton conducting SOFCs (P-SOFCs) demonstrate advantages over oxygen-ion conducting SOFCs, such as less activation energies on ionic transport and higher fuel utilization efficiency.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode

Sentencas: Central to the devices is a suitable cathode with high catalytic activity.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode

Sentencas: Herein, a cubic perovskite BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-delta (BCFSc) has been applied as the cathode in proton-conducting solid state fuel cell (SOFC) with BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY) electrolyte.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode

Sentencas: Peak power densities of 760, 591, 452 and 318 mW cm(-2) are obtained at 650, 600, 550 and 500 degrees C with humidified hydrogen as the fuel and air as the oxidant.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode

Sentencas: A low polarization resistance of 0.05 Omega cm(2) under open circuit at 650 degrees C is observed.
Titulo: High performance of protonic solid oxide fuel cell with BaCo0.7Fe0.22Sc0.08O3-δ electrode
